By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has announced the confirmation of 506 new cases of COVID-19; adding that it has discharged 113,525 patients since the index case was reported in February 27 last year. Releasing the report via it’s twitter handle on Sunday, the health agency also informed that it has confirmed a total of 139,748 cases from across the various isolation facilities in Nigeria. The NCDC regrettably reported that 1,667 lives have been lost to the COVID-19 related complications in Nigeria. According to the report, the fresh cases were recorded from twenty states including the FCT as follows; Ondo-90; Kwara-89; Rivers-53; Borno-45; Gombe-32; FCT-28; Imo-26 and Ogun-25.  Other states where the infections were reported are: Kaduna and Kano-14 each; Edo-13; Osun-11; Cross River-10; Yobe-9;Ekiti-7; Kebbi and Nasarawa-6; Oyo-5 and Jigawa-1. The health agency further gave the state by state breakdown of the total confirmed cases as shown below: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has confirmed 676 new cases of #COVID-19 in Nigeria. The 676 confirmed cases were recorded from 19 states with Lagos State - the epicentre of the novel virus infection leading the table with 227 cases followed by… In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  Nigeria's confirmed COVID-19 infections figure shrunk to  58 new cases on Sunday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has said. According to the report released by the NCDC, the newly recorded cases brought the total confirmed cases to 59,345 out of which… In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Wednesday said it has confirmed 1,138 fresh infections and have so far discharged a total of 108,657 patients since the index case was reported in February 27, 2020 in the country. The new confirmed cases brought… In "Top Stories"